stress may produce excess autophagy, which unselectively
degrades not only malfolded protein aggregates but also
intracellular contents and induces severe neurodegeneration
during excessive autophagic cell death. autophagy may be
protective in initial stages of polyq-induced er stress,12 but
may be deleterious in later stages.2
